**Issue proposal** (for patches to wins.json or sections.json):
Write a proposal file to `monitor/analyst/issue-proposals/` (create dir if needed):
```bash
node -e "
const fs=require('fs');
const dir='monitor/analyst/issue-proposals';
if(!fs.existsSync(dir))fs.mkdirSync(dir,{recursive:true});
const ts=new Date().toISOString().replace(/[:.]/g,'-').slice(0,19);
fs.writeFileSync(dir+'/proposal-'+ts+'.json',JSON.stringify({
  source:'analyst-change-analysis',
  severity:'medium',
  category:'content-update',
  summary:'Brief description',
  detail:'Specific details: what text, what file, what fix',
  affected_wins:['NNN'],
  created_at:new Date().toISOString()
},null,2));
"
```
The decider picks up issue proposals from `monitor/analyst/issue-proposals/` and creates formal issues in `open-issues.json`. Do NOT write directly to `monitor/decisions/open-issues.json` — it is git-owned by the decider.
